nodes.title: Uniform Context Options
widgets_values:
Useful for making animations longer than 16 frames.

If using v2 models, you can connect the LoRA Loader to Motion_Lora


Use Motion_Pe_Stretch higher values to slow motion as well as motion_scale (I think). If motion is too slow it will look choppy.
I have adapted another's workflow but found that ReActor did a far more consistent job but you can un-bypass if this is of interest.

nodes.title: Number of Frames
widgets_values:
This is the total frames the final video will have. We also end the last keyframe on this value. 

I generally add 5-10 or more frames at the end if doing a morph as it seems to always want to loop back.
You could bypass the SkinDiff Detail but I note that it adds back some realism after ReActor.
